  "source": "Theorem: \"Theorem 3.24\"\ngiven: k, m is \\set.theoretic.natural.number\nthen:\n. have:\n  . exists: n is \\set.theoretic.natural.number\n    suchThat:\n    . \\set.theoretic.zero \\:less.than?:/ n\n    . \\sum:of{k}:and{n} = m\n  iff: k \\:less.than?:/ m\nDocumented:\n. description: \"For $k, m \\in \\omega$, $k < m$ if and only if there exists $n \\in \\omega$ such that $n > 0$ and $k + n = m$. This characterizes the order in terms of addition.\"\nId: \"75998e66-ce46-4620-9229-ea57b88168ae\"",
